description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting secondment opportunity has arisen for a proactive, highly motivated and passionate individualon Older Persons Medicine, Ward 31.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic individual to lead the nursing team within our unit. The post holder will have excellent communication skills and have the ability, drive and enthusiasm to motivate and drive an enthusiastic team to provide high quality patient care and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Sister / Charge Nurse will have overall responsibility for the management of the clinical area including assessment of care needs, the development, implementation and evaluation of programmes of care and the setting of standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Sister/ Charge Nurse will participate in innovation and evidence based nursing practice through professional leadership and supports the clinical team by working closely with their Junior Sister team. As a credible and professional role model, you will encourage and empower other staff to develop both personally and professionally to achieve their maximum potential within this exciting area of Older Persons Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
